Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 1cm slices, then chop
into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel). Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}.
Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out
in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Peel the @garlic cloves{2}, pop into a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of oil
and scrunch to enclose it. Add to the chips' baking tray and roast until soft,
~{10-12%minutes}. Meanwhile, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped)
(stalks and all). Zest and halve the @lemon{1}(zested and halved). Pop the
@panko breadcrumbs{25%g} into a #small bowl{} with half the parsley and half the
lemon zest. Add the @olive oil{1%tsp} for the crumb and mix to combine.

Lay the @sea bass fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto a baking tray lined with
#baking paper{}. Spoon a third of the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} over the flesh of the
fish and spread evenly, covering the top. Spoon the breadcrumb mixture on top of
the mayonnaise. Press it down with a #spoon{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

When the oven is hot, bake the fish on the middle shelf until the crumbs are
golden and the fish is cooked, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Once the garlic is cooked, remove from the foil and mash with a #fork{}. Pop it
into a small bowl. Add the remaining @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, parsley and lemon zest.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix to combine.

Squeeze half the lemon juice into a large #bowl{}. Add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for
the dressing. Season with salt, pepper and @?sugar{pinch}, then mix to combine.
Cut the remaining lemon into wedges.

Once everything is ready, add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} to the dressing bowl and
toss to coat. Divide the fish between your plates with the chips, salad and
zesty garlic mayo alongside. Serve with the lemon wedges for squeezing over.
Enjoy!